(Alumni Connect is a role-based full-stack web platform designed to connect) Tj
T* (students, alumni, and administrators in one career-oriented ecosystem. The) Tj
T* (project combines mentoring, job discovery, community interaction, profile) Tj
T* (management, administrative control, and AI-assisted productivity tools) Tj
T* (inside a single application.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10.8 Tf
12.4199999999999999 TL
0.2 0.255 0.333 rg
45.354330708661422 622.7718897637794271 Td
(From the codebase, the project is built with a React frontend and a Flask backend, using MongoDB as the) Tj
T* (main datastore. Authentication is handled through JWT tokens stored in HttpOnly cookies, which gives the) Tj
T* (application a session-based feel while still using token-based authorization under the hood. The system) Tj
T* (also includes Socket.IO for realtime communication and a Gemini-backed optional AI layer for selected) Tj
T* (features.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10.8 Tf
12.4199999999999999 TL
0.2 0.255 0.333 rg
45.354330708661422 539.4333070866141497 Td
(In practical terms, the platform is trying to solve a real campus problem: students often need direct access) Tj
T* (to alumni guidance, verified mentors, role-relevant opportunities, and resume support, while) Tj
T* (administrators need visibility, control, and moderation tools to keep the ecosystem useful and safe.) Tj
